Your cumulative GPA will be used as part of the admission committee's review. Currently, the average admitted GPA is 3.3. If lower than the average we look at other factors. For more information, please click here

The MS MKT program has no course prerequisites. Students may apply with any undergraduate degree. For more information, please click here

Internships may be taken for up to 3 credit hours. Students must be registered with the Career Center's Handshake to apply. International students can only do an internship after completing 2 long semesters (fall and spring). For more information, please go here. For information about internship placement rates, please go here

The MS in Marketing degree can help with both career advancement and earning potential. National statistics show that a Masters degree can on average increase working graduate salaries by 15%. To see job statistics and placement data please see our career outcomes page
Our program has no preference between the GMAT or the GRE. We accept both, for details on the exams please visit the link
Students may apply with any undergraduate degree. No work experience is necessary. For more information about admissions requirements, please click here
Loans apply only to U.S. citizens and permanent residents only: for information about available financial aid programs, please click here
To view our recorded infosessions or to sign-up for a live online Q & A session, please please click here

Our MS MKT degree has 6 career-enhancing tracks and more than 60 electives to choose from. The program totals 36 semester-credit-hours. Our classes are offered on-campus in the evening (many are available online and the entire degree can be completed online) and are especially suitable for students working full-time or part-time jobs. For degree plan information, please click here
You can ask various questions regarding the MS in Marketing program: the curriculum, tuition costs, class profiles salary outcomes, the application processes and many more.

The Fast Track in MS Marketing allows UTD undergraduate students to start on their MS Marketing degree before graduation, saving time and money Students meeting the eligibility requirements can enter our program without a GMAT or GRE score. For more information, please go here

Students may apply with unofficial transcripts. However, no admitted student will be allowed to register for classes until UTD receives the official transcripts. For more information please click here
Under the Choice Act, qualified veterans, spouses, and dependents are eligible for in-state tuition at UTD regardless of their state of residence. For more information, please click here
Please have official transcripts mailed to: The University of Texas at Dallas, Admission & Enrollment Services, 800 W. Campbell Road (ROC 11), Richardson, TX 75080-3021. Please click here
For any other questions, please email msmarketing\@utdallas.edu. You can also request more information by clicking here

Our MS Marketing students represent a wide range of experiences, ages, nationalities, and career goals. The strength of our program comes from the diversity and quality of our student body, faculty, and school. For student profile data about MS MKT students,please click here
Completion of Level 112 at an ELS Language Center is accepted. For more information, please click here
To view and apply for graduate scholarships, please click on the link below. You must have at least submitted your application before you can apply for a scholarship link
MS Marketing is NOT a STEM program. Some students pursue double-degrees, combining MS MKT with a STEM-eligible MS program. For a list of STEM-eligible programs, please click here
IELTS minimum score: 6.5. For more information, please click here
TOEFL minimum scores: 80 (Internet-based test); 550 (paper-based test). For more information, please click here
For answers to our most frequently asked questions, please click here
PTE minimum score: 67 For more information, please click here
Fall semester application deadline: May 1. Spring semester deadline: October 1. Summer semester deadline: March 1. For more information, please click here

Our M.S. in Marketing has several student ambassadors chartered to provide help and information via email for new or prospective students on various topics, including the Dallas environment, housing, living expenses, academic and social life. To contact one of our student ambassadors, please click here

The average admitted GMAT score is 600. Our code is: ZTZPQ23. This requirement may be waived if a student has a cumulative GPA of 3.4 or better from an AACSB school. For more information, please click here
The MS in Marketing can be completed entirely online, the online only option has the same five core courses and over 20 online elective courses to choose from. For more information, please click here
